Rating: 3
Wanting to make something very budget-friendly this week for dinner, we decided to make this, and it was definitely a keeper! Recipe is more like a framework, and it just needed a few embellishments to be fab. Low on the "messing up kitchen" scale, easy 15 minute prep, and great leftovers. Added sauteed onions, green pepper and garlic to the ground beef (1 lb was plenty), made sure to moisten the tortillas with some broth and juice from the tomatoes, added cilantro, several chili-type spices incl chipotle chili powder. This was not at all bland, and our unexpected company who stopped by and ate with us (a grad from culinary institute) said it was, "amazing". This one's going in the recipe box.

