Loved it. Didn't want the beans, but sauted a large diced bell pepper with onion & beef(1 1/2 lb). Softened tortillas w/a little canola oil in non-stick pan. Used grated monterey jack over meat. Covered all w/Hatch mild red enchilada sauce w/grated sharp cheddar & olives. SHOULD HAVE put some sauce on bottom of pan as the tortillas got VERY crisp. Made vinegary red cabbage slaw & sliced avocado. Deeelicious.

Rating: 4
I found this recipe to be very good.... If my boyfriend who is Mexican enjoyed it, then it's a winner in this household. I did make some changes. I dipped the tortillas that I had cut in half in enchilada sause and doubled them for each layer. Once the meat and onions were cooked, I added two taco season packages with the required amount of water. I stirred in the beans to the meat and layered the mixture on top of the tortillas. Next topping the mixture with cheese then mexican corn. I added a second layer the same as the first. I topped this last layer with 1 can of the mexican style stewed tomatoes and 1 can of rotel tomatoes, juice and all. After it had baked for 45 minutes I sprinkled a top layer of Monterey Jack cheese and place back in the oven for approx 10 minutes. This recipe made enough for a 13x9 pan and also a small loaf pan to freeze for another night. I find it a challenge to find different Mexican dishes that my sweetie will enjoy and I must say, this was a winner.

