Rating: 3
I have learned to read other cooks' comments every time; they are often helpful. I wanted a recipe like this but immediately thought it would need more "spicing up." The other cooks' ideas are right on the mark. What I did: made this with Chef Dean Fearing's Turtle Creek black beans layered over the meat. Very easy: cook 3 strips bacon (chopped), add 2 cans black beans (rinsed), chopped onion & garlic & jalapeno, 2 cups chicken broth, simmer 20 minutes or 'til liquid is cooked down. The flavor is fantastic, and it works perfectly in this casserole.

