Good. Everyone liked it, which is unusual in my house. I made many of the same substitutions/additions as other reviewers--garlic, cilantro, packaged taco seasoning in the meat (also added a dollop of Trader Joe's Chipotle Grilling Sauce); dipped tortillas in enchilada sauce; used diced tomatoes with green chilis in place of stewed; black beans, and pre-packaged shredded Mexican cheese blend. Also added a whole bag of frozen southwest-mix veggies (beans, corn, onion, poblano chilis, diced pepper) to the layers (could have skipped one can of black beans because of this addition). Needed just a bit more moisture; next time I'll use the 1/4 cup water the taco seasoning packet calls for in the meat mixture, and add more cheese to the layers.

