Rating: 4
I love this recipe! It's quick and easy, and re-heats very well (great to deliver to new moms, etc.) I made two changes: I used 1/2 to 2/3 of the beef called for, and I use either salsa or Delmonte tomatoes with jalapenos instead of plain stewed tomatoes. If you like things spicy, use all salsa for sure. Also, can be done with flour tortillas if you're out of corn. Someone commented that 1/4 cup of chili powder must be a typo -- it definitely ISN'T. Use it for sure, plus some of your other faves if you like it spicy. The torillas turn out moist -- some would say soggy -- but taste delicious because they've absorbed the dishes flavors. Play around and add your favorite Mexican items.

