Rating: 3
Alright, MY version is a three forker!! I ditch the canned tomatoes and kidney beans and use canned enchilada sauce, extra cheese, garlic, olives and onion. I dip the torts in the heated sauce and layer it up. I saute the meat with the onion and carlic and spice it up with ancho chili paste. I throw sliced black olives in on every layer with more gooey cheese. Right before I do the next layer I spoon on extra enchilada sauce. I often make this with chicken stewed in adobo sauce. Let it sit for 10 or so minutes before cutting or it does not hold its shape. Serve with Sour Cream and some good salsa. You could also add cilantro. There are a million versions. Great for crowds. Fun to make.

